You're always givinâ€™ me ifs.

01:26:30.120 --> 01:26:32.000
I can't eat ifs
and neither can you,

01:26:32.040 --> 01:26:35.040
while Julia Rainbird and you
are waltzinâ€™ around
in the great beyond.

01:26:35.080 --> 01:26:38.120
Come on, sweetheart. The least
I can do is show up for work
every now and then.

01:26:38.200 --> 01:26:40.320
After all, didn't I give you
the guy's name?

01:26:40.360 --> 01:26:42.520
But the phone book is full
of Arthur Adamsons.

01:26:42.600 --> 01:26:46.280
It's very simple.
All you need to do
is find out the right one.

01:26:46.320 --> 01:26:49.120
That's a snap.
The one that's
close to 40 years old...

01:26:49.160 --> 01:26:51.120
and trembles a little bit
at the name Eddie Shoebridge.

01:26:51.200 --> 01:26:54.080
Easy. We do that tomorrow.
Now would be much better.

01:26:54.120 --> 01:26:57.040
A bird in the hand,
Lumley. Please.
Oh, sweetheart.

01:26:57.120 --> 01:26:59.160
The only bird that's
gonna be in my hand...

01:26:59.240 --> 01:27:01.120
and I'm very sorry
to say this...

01:27:01.200 --> 01:27:03.400
is a steering wheel
from 4:00 to midnight.

01:27:04.920 --> 01:27:07.720
Sure.
Why should I get a kiss?

01:27:07.760 --> 01:27:10.200
Just when I was
beginning to think
you werenâ€™t impossible.

01:27:10.280 --> 01:27:12.120
Maybe I'll do it
without you.

01:27:12.200 --> 01:27:14.160
The hell you will!

01:27:14.240 --> 01:27:16.080
Come on, now. Please.

01:27:16.160 --> 01:27:19.160
This Shoebridge fellow's
gone to a lot of trouble
not to be found.

01:27:19.240 --> 01:27:22.400
<i>Now you got no idea what kind
of trouble you could get into.</i>

01:27:22.440 --> 01:27:24.840
Whatever it is,
he'll forget about it...

01:27:24.920 --> 01:27:27.240
when he hears about
the millions he's coming into.

01:27:27.280 --> 01:27:29.320
Oh, Blanche, come on.

01:27:29.400 --> 01:27:33.560
Just sit down on your
pretty little... behind.

01:27:33.640 --> 01:27:35.880
And I must say,
it is quite an...

01:27:35.920 --> 01:27:38.280
No, it is.
Very attractive
little behind.

01:27:38.360 --> 01:27:40.360
Just wait for me,
okay?

01:27:40.440 --> 01:27:44.880
And tonight when I get home,
we will, uh...

01:27:44.960 --> 01:27:48.280
Right. Very nice.
Plot our strategy.

01:27:48.360 --> 01:27:50.320
Know what I mean,
darlinâ€™?

01:28:05.120 --> 01:28:06.960
Who needs him.

01:28:17.480 --> 01:28:20.400
You wouldn't be
Arthur Adamson,
would you?

01:28:20.480 --> 01:28:22.320
Excuse me.

01:28:27.560 --> 01:28:29.440
Excuse me!

01:28:32.160 --> 01:28:35.000
Hello. Are you
Arthur Adamson?

01:28:35.080 --> 01:28:36.920
Hey, Art!

01:28:38.680 --> 01:28:40.520
Yeah?

01:28:54.280 --> 01:28:56.120
A.A.?

01:29:04.760 --> 01:29:06.600
I'm sorry.
We're just closing.

01:29:06.680 --> 01:29:10.920
I understand.
I'm not shopping.
Is Mr. Adamson around?

01:29:10.960 --> 01:29:13.480
I'm afraid not. But if you
come back tomorrow...

01:29:13.560 --> 01:29:15.480
All right.

01:29:15.560 --> 01:29:17.960
But just to be sure I have
the right Mr. Adamson,

01:29:18.040 --> 01:29:22.400
he is a gentleman
of about 40, I trust?
Yes, that's about right.

01:29:22.480 --> 01:29:25.440
Oh, that's
the first encouraging news
I've had all afternoon.

01:29:25.520 --> 01:29:28.200
Isn't there someplace
I might reach him
without delay?

01:29:28.280 --> 01:29:30.120
You mean tonight?
Yes.

01:29:30.200 --> 01:29:33.320
Well, he usually goes
directly home from here.

01:29:33.360 --> 01:29:36.680
But tonight would be
very bad because I believe
he's giving a party.

01:29:36.760 --> 01:29:39.800
I know he left unusually
early for some such reason.

01:29:39.880 --> 01:29:42.400
Isn't there something
I can tell him for you
in the morning?

01:29:42.440 --> 01:29:45.880
This is personal.
Rather personal.
Oh, I see.

01:29:45.960 --> 01:29:49.160
Perhaps you'd like
to leave him a note.

01:29:49.200 --> 01:29:51.280
A note? Very good.
Yes. Come this way.

01:29:53.280 --> 01:29:55.120
Excuse me.

01:29:57.360 --> 01:29:59.240
Thank you.

01:30:12.000 --> 01:30:14.280
Is anything the matter?

01:30:14.320 --> 01:30:16.760
Uh, I was, uh,
just thinking.

01:30:16.840 --> 01:30:19.520
Instead of leaving
this note here,

01:30:19.560 --> 01:30:23.560
it might be better
if I sent Mr. Adamson
a telegram tonight.

01:30:23.640 --> 01:30:26.680
<i>What's his address,
please?
Well, I don't...</i>

01:30:26.760 --> 01:30:29.960
It's all right.
We're friends.

01:30:30.040 --> 01:30:32.440
- 1001 Franklin Street.
- 1001 Franklin.

01:30:32.520 --> 01:30:35.160
Thank you very much.
You've been very kind.

01:30:38.080 --> 01:30:40.120
You're a Capricorn,
aren't you?

01:30:40.200 --> 01:30:42.040
No, I'm a Leo.

01:30:43.320 --> 01:30:46.200
That's what I thought.

01:31:01.000 --> 01:31:02.880
Pete, hi.
Hello, there,
Blanche, baby.

01:31:02.960 --> 01:31:06.680
Have you seen George?
He just left a few minutes ago,
but he'll be back.

01:31:06.760 --> 01:31:09.040
Took a party of four
out to River Valley.

01:31:09.120 --> 01:31:12.000
Oh, dear. That could
take all night.
Easily. What's up?

01:31:12.080 --> 01:31:14.280
Would you give him
a message for me?
Sure thing.

01:31:14.320 --> 01:31:16.800
Just tell him
I found him.
You found him?

01:31:16.840 --> 01:31:20.840
That's right.
He lives at 1001 Franklin.
1001 Franklin.

01:31:20.920 --> 01:31:23.280
That's where he lives,
and that's where I'm going now.

01:31:23.360 --> 01:31:25.920
You found him, and
that's where he lives, and
that's where you're going now.

01:31:25.960 --> 01:31:27.880
Thanks, Pete.
Any time, Blanche.

01:31:37.400 --> 01:31:40.040
You wanna go over
the new pickup spot once again?

01:31:40.080 --> 01:31:42.200
I know it by heart.

01:31:42.280 --> 01:31:45.480
Are you all right?

01:31:45.520 --> 01:31:47.880
I will be.
You sure?

01:31:51.560 --> 01:31:54.840
Have to be there at 9:30.
Let's get going.

01:32:31.360 --> 01:32:33.640
Bishop Wood,
it's time to go.

01:32:33.680 --> 01:32:35.760
Have you your vestments on?

01:32:35.840 --> 01:32:38.680
Yes, but I haven't
finished the chicken.

01:32:40.800 --> 01:32:43.680
I'm sorry, Your Excellency.

01:32:43.760 --> 01:32:45.800
Here's what
I want you to do.

01:32:45.880 --> 01:32:48.040
Place the armchair
in the center of the room...

01:32:48.120 --> 01:32:52.000
facing away from the door
and seat yourself in it.

01:32:52.040 --> 01:32:55.440
You're going to be
comfortably put to sleep.

01:32:55.520 --> 01:32:58.720
But it'll last only
for a short while.

01:32:58.760 --> 01:33:03.320
Thank you very much.
You are most considerate.

01:33:03.400 --> 01:33:06.120
Let me know
when you're ready.

01:33:06.160 --> 01:33:09.120
By the way. I haven't quite
finished that book...

01:33:09.160 --> 01:33:11.400
you were kind enough
to let me have.

01:33:11.440 --> 01:33:13.680
May I, uh,
take it along?

01:33:16.800 --> 01:33:19.040
With our fingerprints on it?
Tsk, tsk, tsk.

01:33:19.080 --> 01:33:22.080
Nice try,
Your Excellency.

01:33:22.120 --> 01:33:27.040
Thank you.
Don't bother, then.
I'm ready.

01:33:27.120 --> 01:33:29.440
All right, I'll be
turning your light off now.

01:33:54.520 --> 01:33:57.520
We mustnâ€™t be late.
See who it is,
and be careful.

01:34:27.240 --> 01:34:30.240
It's her. That woman.
Blanche Tyler.

01:34:30.320 --> 01:34:33.560
This is incredible!

01:34:33.640 --> 01:34:36.600
Is that cab driver
with her?
She's alone.

01:34:38.760 --> 01:34:41.760
If I didn't have to make
this pickup in 35 minutes...

01:34:41.800 --> 01:34:44.240
What are we going to do?

01:34:44.320 --> 01:34:46.520
Nothing!

01:34:46.600 --> 01:34:48.400
Until later tonight.

01:35:00.680 --> 01:35:03.320
- She's gone.
- Come on. Let's go.

01:35:03.400 --> 01:35:05.240
<i>Hurry, hurry, hurry!</i>

01:36:18.680 --> 01:36:21.480
I thought you said...
I know.

01:36:21.520 --> 01:36:24.360
- Mr. Adamson?
- Watch him.

01:36:30.680 --> 01:36:34.520
Oh, Mr. Adamson.
How lucky I am
not to have missed you.

01:36:34.600 --> 01:36:37.400
Apparently you didn't hear me
at the front door.
Apparently.

01:36:37.480 --> 01:36:41.120
I am Madame Blanche Tyler,
the spiritualist.

01:36:41.160 --> 01:36:43.360
Good evening, honey.

01:36:43.400 --> 01:36:47.040
Madame Blanche, I wonder if I
might suggest to you to remove
your car from our driveway.

01:36:47.080 --> 01:36:49.880
We're terribly late
for an appointment.
Well, yes.

01:36:49.960 --> 01:36:54.240
When you hear why
I've come, Mr. Adamson...
Or should I say Shoebridge?

01:36:54.280 --> 01:36:56.400
You won't mind
being late at all.
My dear lady,

01:36:56.480 --> 01:36:58.520
I know exactly why
you've come here.
How could you?

01:36:58.600 --> 01:37:01.960
<i>- And exactly why you and
your friend, that cab driver...
- You know George?</i>

01:37:02.040 --> 01:37:06.920
Have been sniffing along my
trail like two eager bloodhounds
these past few weeks.

01:37:07.000 --> 01:37:09.160
I had no idea,
Mr. Adamson.

01:37:09.200 --> 01:37:12.240
All right, Madame Blanche,
you found me.
Music to my ears.

01:37:12.320 --> 01:37:16.840
I'm perfectly willing to listen
to your demands, whatever they
might be, but not right now.

01:37:16.880 --> 01:37:19.760
No demands, Mr. Adamson.
Oh, no, no, no!

01:37:19.840 --> 01:37:23.520
Hardly that. Julia Rainbird
wants nothing from you...

01:37:23.560 --> 01:37:28.040
but the privilege of making you
heir to the entire
Rainbird fortune.

01:37:28.120 --> 01:37:30.200
The whole, lovely
millions and millions of it.

01:37:30.280 --> 01:37:34.600
<i>Now if she made any demands
at all, they were on me
to find you.</i>

01:37:34.680 --> 01:37:37.520
Through psychic means,
of course.

01:37:37.600 --> 01:37:40.360
Let me get this straight.
Is that the only reason
you and your friend have been,

01:37:40.400 --> 01:37:42.280
shall we say,
investigating me?

01:37:42.320 --> 01:37:44.800
<i>Oh, yes. And don't think
it's been easy.</i>

01:37:44.880 --> 01:37:48.120
<i>Oh, Mr. Adamson,
you've given George and me
the devil's own time of it.</i>

01:37:48.200 --> 01:37:50.600
<i>Tracing you
from a foundling baby...</i>

01:37:50.680 --> 01:37:54.880
<i>to a young boy named Shoebridge
to a man named Adamson.</i>

01:37:54.920 --> 01:37:57.640
<i>Oh, but, Mr. Adamson,
here you are,: Here I am.</i>

01:37:57.680 --> 01:38:01.120
<i>- It's a happy moment
for us all, isn't it?
-</i>

01:38:01.200 --> 01:38:03.560
<i>It's the Bishop.</i>

01:38:14.400 --> 01:38:16.680
Does anyone know
that you've come here?

01:38:18.040 --> 01:38:20.520
No one know...

01:38:20.600 --> 01:38:23.280
Anyone kn-know?

01:38:23.360 --> 01:38:26.800
No. Not a soul.

01:38:26.880 --> 01:38:30.120
Not even George soul.

01:38:30.200 --> 01:38:33.320
You have nothing
to worry about, Mr. Adamson.

01:38:34.920 --> 01:38:36.800
I promise.

01:38:39.400 --> 01:38:42.880
I won't breathe a word...
to anyone.

01:39:01.960 --> 01:39:04.200
It looks like Miss Tyler
needs some rest.

01:39:09.560 --> 01:39:11.760
Will you do as I say?

01:39:28.120 --> 01:39:31.680
No. No.

01:40:12.160 --> 01:40:14.000
Unlock the door.

01:40:21.640 --> 01:40:23.480
Cheer up, Fran.

01:40:23.560 --> 01:40:26.280
Let's go get the new diamond
for our chandelier.

01:40:49.520 --> 01:40:52.960
Wow.
It's gorgeous.

01:41:03.080 --> 01:41:05.440
And now for Madame Blanche.

01:46:13.600 --> 01:46:15.520
Oh, my God.

01:46:58.040 --> 01:46:59.880
Blanche?

01:47:10.880 --> 01:47:12.720
Blanche?

01:47:19.920 --> 01:47:21.800
Blanche?

01:47:50.360 --> 01:47:54.280
<i>If I'm talking too much, perhaps
it's because you're not talking.</i>

01:47:54.360 --> 01:47:57.440
It's my stomach, Arthur.
Murder doesn't agree with it.

01:47:57.520 --> 01:48:00.000
You think I'm
looking forward to it?

01:48:00.040 --> 01:48:03.240
<i>If Joe Maloney
had been more efficient,
they'd both be dead by now.</i>

01:48:04.560 --> 01:48:07.040
You can have my share,
Arthur.

01:48:07.120 --> 01:48:11.320
You can keep both diamonds
all to yourself
if you'll just end it.

01:48:12.400 --> 01:48:15.040
<i>I'll tell you what I'll do.</i>

01:48:15.080 --> 01:48:18.080
<i>If you help me carry Sleeping
Beauty up out of the cellar,
load her into our car...</i>

01:48:18.120 --> 01:48:22.120
<i>and drive her out
to some deserted road
where a suicide can take place,</i>

01:48:22.200 --> 01:48:24.440
<i>I promise you we'll talk
this thing over.</i>

01:48:25.640 --> 01:48:28.480
<i>Okay?
What about the cab driver?</i>

01:48:28.560 --> 01:48:32.680
<i>If she was able to find us,
I'm sure he can too.</i>

01:48:32.760 --> 01:48:37.280
<i>He'll walk
right into our hands.
Your hands, not mine.</i>

01:48:37.320 --> 01:48:39.680
<i>Don't you think we ought to
go down and take a look at her?</i>

01:48:39.720 --> 01:48:41.760
It's been a while
since we gave her that shot.

01:48:41.800 --> 01:48:44.960
<i>You do it.
Okay.</i>

01:49:55.840 --> 01:49:58.480
You'll be happy to know
she's still unconscious.

01:50:20.120 --> 01:50:22.560
Blanche.
Shh!

01:50:47.080 --> 01:50:50.560
I'll put this end
into her exhaust pipe...

01:50:50.640 --> 01:50:53.240
and the other end
in the window.

01:50:53.320 --> 01:50:55.840
That way,
it'll look like suicide.

01:51:29.160 --> 01:51:31.240
Better go and get her now.

01:51:31.320 --> 01:51:34.240
I'll take her in our car.
You follow in hers.

01:51:47.040 --> 01:51:48.880
You take hold
of her feet.

01:51:53.640 --> 01:51:56.440
Jesus, she's heavy.

01:51:58.040 --> 01:51:59.880
George!

01:52:01.400 --> 01:52:03.560
Got 'em.

01:52:06.920 --> 01:52:09.280
Blanche, you faked
that one beautifully.

01:52:09.320 --> 01:52:12.120
You are still the champ.

01:52:12.200 --> 01:52:14.560
Thank you, George.

01:52:14.640 --> 01:52:17.640
Do you realize how much
the reward is for those two?

01:52:19.520 --> 01:52:21.400
Yes.

01:52:21.480 --> 01:52:24.880
But do you realize
how much more
the reward would be...

01:52:24.960 --> 01:52:28.320
if we could
find the diamonds
and turn 'em in?

01:52:33.840 --> 01:52:36.480
What's the matter
with you?

01:52:36.560 --> 01:52:38.560
I...

01:52:38.640 --> 01:52:40.520
Blanche,
what's the matter?

01:52:51.240 --> 01:52:53.160
<i>Blanche,
what's the matter?</i>

01:53:06.600 --> 01:53:08.440
What is it?

01:53:37.720 --> 01:53:40.080
Blanche, you did it!

01:53:40.160 --> 01:53:42.000
You are psychic!

01:53:44.280 --> 01:53:46.920
What am I doing here
on the stairs?
You're not a fake.

01:53:47.000 --> 01:53:49.520
You actually found one.
Look.

01:53:49.600 --> 01:53:51.440
I did?

01:53:51.520 --> 01:53:54.280
I'll get the police on the phone
and give them our good news,

01:53:54.360 --> 01:53:57.400
and call Miss Rainbird
and give her the bad.

01:54:04.400 --> 01:54:06.760
Operator,
can I have the police?

